    <name>
      <text>Find the cardinality of the largest possible set</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>(a) Consider the following sets: </p>
<p>\(A={@setA@}\) and \(B={@setB@} \).</p>
<p>Find the cardinality of the largest possible set \(C\) such that \(C \subseteq A\) and \(C \subseteq B\).</p><p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>

<br>

<p>(b) For this part, the universal set is {@univ2@}.</p>
<p>Find examples of sets \(D\) and \(E\) such that \(|D| = {@kk@}\), \(|E| = {@ll@}\) and \(|D \cup E| = {@mm@}\)</p>
<p><em>Note: A set is entered in the blanks using curly brackets notation and double quotes.  As example, we have: <code>{"apple","orange","mango"}</em></code>.</p>
<p>\(D = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]</p>
<p> \(E = \) [[input:ans3]]  [[validation:ans3]] </p>
<p> [[feedback:prt2]] </p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>(a) Consider the following sets: </p>
<p>\(A={@setA@}\) and \(B={@setB@} \).</p>
<p>To find the cardinality of the largest possible set \(C\) such that \(C \subseteq A\) and \(C \subseteq B\), the first step is to determine the set corresponding to \( A \cap B\).</p>
<p>We have: \( A \cap B = {@intAB@}\) and Card\((A \cap B)={@ta1@} \). Therefore, the cardinality of the largest possible set \(C\) satisfying the given condition above is \({@ta1@}\).</p>

<br>

<p>(b) For this part, the universal set is {@univ2@}.</p>
<p>Let find examples of sets \(D\) and \(E\) such that \(|D| = {@kk@}\), \(|E| = {@ll@}\) and \(|D \cup E| = {@mm@}\)</p>
<p>There are many possible ways to write the sets \(D\) and \(E\) in this case. Thus, we can choose:</p>
<p>\(D={@set_D@}\) and \(E={@set_E@}\). Then  \(D \cup E = {@set_DUE@}\).]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
